est. autem quaedam: the ‘soundness of mind' resulting from the harmony of all its parts belongs only to the sapiens; but a special kind of it, though of a lower order, may be seen even in one who is not sapiens when, after a fit of insanity, the faculties are restored to their normal state by medical treatment : the health of mind which the sapiens enjoys is as sar above the state of mind of the insipiens as sanity in the ordinary use of the word is above insanity.
